{
  "stem": "1799.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'm going to London, and then I'm going to stay in the neighborhood of London.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was in early December of 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In April of 1939, my father was released from his prison sentence of-- end period.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He came out and was given 48 hours to leave Germany, which was the second major blow to him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The handwriting was not only on the wall, it was indelible by then.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He had no way, neither emotionally nor financially, to just leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So my mother, again, went about to acquire a passport that he needed, an exit visa, and tickets to leave-- first to Paris, and then from Marseilles, the port in southern France, to take a ship to Bolivia, which was the only thing she could get.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "What she didn't realize-- and I say this in hindsight, because I didn't know it then-- is that the only way that could have happened smoothly is if she would have planned to go with him, but she did not.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And so by sending him, in that April, 1938, to France with a ticket to take a train in Marseilles, she also did great harm to that relationship-- their, their-- it pointed it out to me later on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It might be that, at that point, their marriage also was not that good, so my father got a double blow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He didn't know it, at first.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He didn't know that she wasn't planning on coming, but he was given the 48 hours, and therefore, he had to-- the Germans were very strict.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had to just leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was still in the orphanage, and I did not see my father before he left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had never visited him in prison.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
